<title>SOUTH AFRICA: Mathomo interim shr rises, no div.</title>
<headline>Mathomo interim shr rises, no div.</headline>
<dateline>JOHANNESBURG 1997-06-25</dateline>
<text>
<p>Half-year ended March 31</p>
<p>			(million rand unless stated)</p>
<p>    Shr, attrib (cts)	 13.4	vs    7.8</p>
<p>    Attrib income	     5.92	vs    2.86</p>
<p>    Pre-tax		     8.63	vs    3.84</p>
<p>    Tax			   2.66	vs    0.98</p>
<p>    Interest paid	     4.07	vs    2.18</p>
<p>    Turnover		  113.70	vs    49.70</p>
<p>Full name: Mathomo Group Ltd (stores)</p>
<p>NOTE - The company said no interim dividend had been declared in terms of company policy. It said due to the seasonal nature of its trade, operating income would be higher in the second half of the year. In addition, the interest charge would be lower due to the redemption of certain high interest bearing debt.</p>
<p>-- Johannesburg newsroom +27 11 482 1003</p>
